World Cup hopefuls Sweden are facing an injury  setback here on Friday following their international friendly against Denmark.
Defender Roger Ljung was operated on a fractured cheek bone after Sweden's  1-0 defeat at Copenhagen while Napoli-based Jonas Thern is undergoing  physiotherapy after straining a ligament in his left foot.
Pontus Kaamark ended the match with concussion and is not expected to  train for five days.
Thern is expected to rejoin the tean on June 3 at Varberg.
